  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Cylinder Head Removal and Installation"
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Fuel feed tube must be removed after releasing fuel pressure.",
        "Fire is strictly prohibited.",
        "If the radiator cap is removed when the water temperature is high, the coolant is under pressure and may spurt out. After the water temperature drops, wrap the cap with a piece of cloth and open it gently."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Since metallic sodium is sealed in the exhaust valve, refer to \"Precautions in the Workplace and Precautions when Handling Metallic Sodium Enclosed Valves\" for inspection and maintenance."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Use fender covers and do not scratch painted surfaces.",
        "Cylinder head removal must always be performed when the engine is cold (below 38°C) to avoid heat distortion.",
        "Do not bend the cylinder head gasket as a metal gasket is used.",
        "Do not scratch or dent the cylinder head and cylinder gasket mating surfaces.",
        "Do not allow coolant to adhere to electrical components or painted surfaces. If it does adhere, wipe it off immediately.",
        "Keep magnetized objects away from the cam chain.",
        "O-rings and gaskets must be replaced with new ones when disassembling."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "When disconnecting wires, couplers and hoses for each sensor, mark them so that they cannot be mistaken during installation."
    },
