    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Remove the rocker arm (A) and hydraulic tappet (B)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "16. Cylinder head removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "372_5.0_jpn_11582834_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Loosen the cylinder head bolts several times in numerical order."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Cylinder Head Mounting"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "372_5.0_jpn_11582835_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Clean the mounting surfaces of the cylinder head and cylinder block. Install the knock pin (A) and a new cylinder head gasket (B) into the cylinder block."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Cylinder head Bolt inspection"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Cylinder head bolts shall be replaced when the most detailed outside diameter of the threads is below the limit value. Limit value: 1 7.62mm"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Cylinder head bolt tightening (when replacing cylinder head bolts)"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "372_5.0_jpn_11582836_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Apply engine oil to the threads and washer seat surface of the cylinder head bolts, install them, and tighten them in the order of their number to 20 N-m (2.0 kgf-m)."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Use a plate type torque wrench whenever possible.",
        "If a bolt squeaks, loosen it once and retighten it."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "Use a plate type torque wrench whenever possible."
        },
        {
          "text": "Use a plate type torque wrench whenever possible."
        },
        {
          "text": "If a bolt squeaks, loosen it once and retighten it."
        },
        {
          "text": "If a bolt squeaks, loosen it once and retighten it."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "372_5.0_jpn_11582837_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "2",
      "text": "Tighten the cylinder head bolts 210° in numerical order."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "372_5.0_jpn_11582838_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "3",
      "text": "Loosen the cylinder head bolts several times in numerical order. Tighten the cylinder head bolts again following steps 1 and 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "4. Cylinder head bolt tightening (when cylinder head bolts are reused)"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "372_5.0_jpn_11582839_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Apply engine oil to the threads and washer seat surface of the cylinder head bolts, and tighten them in the order of their number to 20 N-m (2.0 kgf-m)."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Use a plate type torque wrench whenever possible.",
        "If a bolt squeaks, loosen it once and retighten it."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "Use a plate type torque wrench whenever possible."
        },
        {
          "text": "Use a plate type torque wrench whenever possible."
        },
        {
          "text": "If a bolt squeaks, loosen it once and retighten it."
        },
        {
          "text": "If a bolt squeaks, loosen it once and retighten it."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "372_5.0_jpn_11582840_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "2",
      "text": "Tighten the cylinder head bolts 210° in numerical order."
    },
